example using PostgreSQL: 

1. Insert the image into the table:
  - Replace '/path/to/your/sar_image' with the actual path to your SAR image file. 
  - The lo_import function in PostgreSQL is used to import large objects (binary files) into a database.

INSERT INTO sar_raw (sRaster) VALUES (lo_import('/path/to/your/sar_image'));


2. Retrieve the SAR image from the table:
  - Replace <image_id> with the ID of the SAR image you want to retrieve.
  
SELECT sRaster FROM sar_raw WHERE id = <image_id>;
